    <text>
        <body>
            <entry xml:id="entry_fycyn" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>fycyn</orth><form type="participle"
                            ><orth>fyx(t)</orth></form></form>
                <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>ficun</orth><form
                        type="participle"><orth>funx(t)</orth></form></form>
                <sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>варить(ся)</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>cook</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>кипятить</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>boil</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>кипеть</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>seethe</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>печь(ся)</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>bake</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>īnnæ avd (læppūjy) æddædær axodæn fycync</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>другие семь (юношей) подальше варят завтрак</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>the other seven (boys) are making breakfast farther away</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>64</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>æxsavær ysfyxtoj</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>сварили ужин</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>the dinner was cooked</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Munk."/><biblScope>22</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>afycoj qædurtæ, abadūt æncad</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>(пока) сварятся бобы, посидите спокойно</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>while the beans are cooking, sit still</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>44</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>...funxtæj wæ guboræ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>...пекся ваш чурек</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>...your churek (flat armenian bread with sesame seeds) was baked</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Gurdž._Saxi_ræs."
                                /><biblScope>4</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>argævstoj fys, yskodtoj fīzonǵytæ æmæ sfyxtoj fyd</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>зарезали барана, сделали шашлыки и сварили мясо</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>they slaughtered a ram, made kebabs and boiled its meat</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ОЭ"/><biblScope>I 48</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>xædzīlgæ waxstytæ artmæ zīlync æmæ fycync</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>самовертящиеся вертелы вращаются над огнем и жарят (шашлык)</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>self-rotating skewers rotate over the fire and grill (a kebub)</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ЮОПам."/><biblScope>II
                            9</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Восходит к <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
                        <w>*pač-, *pak-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ine"><lang/>
                        <w>*pek˳-</w>
                        <gloss><q>жечь</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ine"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>варить</q></gloss></mentioned>. Ожидали бы ос. %i*fæc-%i.
                    Огласовка %iу%i (%ifyc-%i), д. %iu%i (%ifunx%i) могла возникнуть из %ia%i в
                    соседстве губного, как в <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fys"/> | %ifus%i из
                    %ipasu%i, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_myd"/> | %imud%i из %imadu-%i и др. В
                    этом случае огласовку %ii%i в д. %ific-%i надо считать вторичной (перед %ic%i,
                    как в превербе %iis-%i из %iuz-%i перед %is%i?). Прош. причастие %ifyx%i |
                    %ifunx%i сопоставляется с <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>pakva-</w></mentioned> с вторичной вставкой %in%i в дигорском.<note
                        type="footnote" n="1"> PUT NOTE HERE </note> Соответствия в иранских и
                    индоевропейских языках: <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>puxtan : paz-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><lang/>
                        <w>puxtan : paz-</w>
                        <gloss><q>варить</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>печь</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ku"><lang/>
                        <w>patin : piʒ-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-balochi"><lang/>
                        <w>pāčag</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ps"><lang/>
                        <w>paxawəl</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="prc"><lang/>
                        <w>peč</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sgh"><lang/>
                        <w>piʒ : paxt-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"><lang/>
                        <w>pac-</w>
                        <gloss><q>варить</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"
                            ><w>peš-</w>
                        <gloss><q>зреть</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="yah"><lang/>
                        <w>paʒ- : pux-</w>
                        <gloss><q>варить</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="yah"><w>paš :
                            pux</w>
                        <gloss><q>спеть</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Андреев._Язг."/><biblScope>4–5</biblScope></bibl>),
                        <mentioned xml:lang="yai"><lang/>
                        <w>pač- : puxt</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>*pač- (pč-)</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/>
                        <w>pajs-</w>
                        <gloss><q>варить</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>печь</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"
                            ><w>pachāre</w>
                        <gloss><q>они пекут</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_BSOS"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">VIII 131
                            сл.</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">VIII 131
                    ff.</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>pač-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>pač- : pakva-</w>
                        <gloss><q>печь</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>варить</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/>
                        <w>печь, пеку</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sqj"><lang/>
                        <w>pjek</w>
                        <gloss><q>пеку</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/>
                        <w>coquo</w>
                        <gloss><q>пеку</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>варю</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/>
                        <w>πέσσω</w>
                        <gloss><q>варю</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>перевариваю</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-tchr"><lang/>
                        <w>pak-, päk-, päkw-</w>
                        <gloss><q>вариться</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-tchr"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>зреть</q></gloss></mentioned>. Для %ifyx%i | %ifunx%i ср., помимо
                        <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>pakva-</w></mentioned>, еще <mentioned xml:lang="ps"><lang/>
                        <w>pōx</w>
                        <gloss><q>печеный</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ps"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>зрелый</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sgh"><lang/>
                        <w>pēx</w>
                        <gloss><q>зрелый</q></gloss></mentioned>. Для перебоя %iа%i → %iu%i ср.
                        <mentioned xml:lang="fa" extralang="pal"><lang/>
                        <w>puxt-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>pwγš-</w>
                        <gloss><q>котелок для варки</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="sog"><w>pwγtʼkʼry</w>
                        <gloss><q>варка</q></gloss></mentioned>. Обращает на себя внимание близость
                    к иранскому соответствующих глаголов в пермских языках: <mentioned xml:lang="kv"><lang/>
                        <w n="0">пузь-</w>
                        <gloss><q>кипятить</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kv"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>кипеть</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kv"
                            ><w n="0">пöж-</w>
                        <gloss><q>па́рить</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kv"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>печь</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="udm"><lang/>
                        <w n="0">пыж-</w>
                        <gloss><q>печь</q></gloss></mentioned>.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II 54</biblScope></bibl>;
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."
                            /><biblScope>18</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."/><biblScope>67</biblScope></bibl>. —
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
                        /><biblScope>24</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><author>Gershevitch</author><ref
                            type="bibl" target="#ref_BSOAS"/><biblScope>XVII
                    479</biblScope></bibl>.),</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">It traces back to <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
                        <w>*pač-, *pak-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ine"><lang/>
                        <w>*pek˳-</w>
                        <gloss><q>burn</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ine"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>boil</q></gloss></mentioned>. The expected Ossetic form is
                    %i*fæc-%i. The vowel %iу%i (%ifyc-%i), Digor %iu%i (%ifunx%i) could have
                    appeared from %ia%i in the neighbourhood of a labial consonant, as in <ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_fys"/> | %ifus%i from %ipasu%i, <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_myd"/> | %imud%i from %imadu-%i etc. In this case the vowel
                    %ii%i in Digor %ific-%i should be considered secondary (before %ic%i, as in the
                    preverb %iis-%i from %iuz-%i before %is%i?). A past participle %ifyx%i |
                    %ifunx%i is compared with <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>pakva-</w></mentioned> with the secondary insertion of %in%i in
                        Digor.<note type="footnote" n="1"> PUT NOTE HERE </note> Correspondences in
                    Iranian and Indo-European languages: <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>puxtan : paz-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><lang/>
                        <w>puxtan : paz-</w>
                        <gloss><q>boil</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>bake</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ku"><lang/>
                        <w>patin : piʒ-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-balochi"><lang/>
                        <w>pāčag</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ps"><lang/>
                        <w>paxawəl</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="prc"><lang/>
                        <w>peč</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sgh"><lang/>
                        <w>piʒ : paxt-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"><lang/>
                        <w>pac-</w>
                        <gloss><q>варить</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"
                            ><w>peš-</w>
                        <gloss><q>ripen</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="yah"><lang/>
                        <w>paʒ- : pux-</w>
                        <gloss><q>boil</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="yah"><w>paš :
                            pux</w>
                        <gloss><q>ripen</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Андреев._Язг."/><biblScope>4–5</biblScope></bibl>),
                        <mentioned xml:lang="yai"><lang/>
                        <w>pač- : puxt</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>*pač- (pč-)</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/>
                        <w>pajs-</w>
                        <gloss><q>boil</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>bake</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"
                            ><w>pachāre</w>
                        <gloss><q>they are baking</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_BSOS"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">VIII 131
                            сл.</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">VIII 131
                    ff.</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>pač-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>pač- : pakva-</w>
                        <gloss><q>bake</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>варить</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/>
                        <w>pečʼ, peku</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sqj"><lang/>
                        <w>pjek</w>
                        <gloss><q>I am baking</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/>
                        <w>coquo</w>
                        <gloss><q>I am baking</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>I am boiling</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/>
                        <w>πέσσω</w>
                        <gloss><q>I am boiling</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>I am reboiling</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="x-tchr"><lang/>
                        <w>pak-, päk-, päkw-</w>
                        <gloss><q>be boiling</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-tchr"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>ripen</q></gloss></mentioned>. For %ifyx%i | %ifunx%i, besides
                        <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>pakva-</w></mentioned>, cf. also <mentioned xml:lang="ps"><lang/>
                        <w>pōx</w>
                        <gloss><q>baked</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ps"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>ripe</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sgh"><lang/>
                        <w>pēx</w>
                        <gloss><q>ripe</q></gloss></mentioned>. For the alteration %iа%i → %iu%i cf.
                        <mentioned xml:lang="fa" extralang="pal"><lang/>
                        <w>puxt-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>pwγš-</w>
                        <gloss><q>cooking pot</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"
                            ><w>pwγtʼkʼry</w>
                        <gloss><q>cooking</q></gloss></mentioned>. The closeness of the
                    corresponding verbs in the Permian languages to Iranian is noteworthy:
                        <mentioned xml:lang="kv"><lang/>
                        <w>puź-</w>
                        <gloss><q>boil</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kv"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>boil</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kv"><w>pöž-</w>
                        <gloss><q>steam</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kv"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>bake</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="udm"><lang/>
                        <w>pyž-</w>
                        <gloss><q>bake</q></gloss></mentioned>.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II 54</biblScope></bibl>;
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."
                            /><biblScope>18</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."/><biblScope>67</biblScope></bibl>. —
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
                        /><biblScope>24</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><author>Gershevitch</author><ref
                            type="bibl" target="#ref_BSOAS"/><biblScope>XVII
                    479</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
                <note type="footnote" xml:lang="ru" n="1"><bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Gershevitch"/></bibl> возводит %ifyc-%i к %ipaxš-%i, как
                    %idūc-%i [см. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_dūcyn"/>] к %iduxš-%i (<bibl><ref
                            type="bibl" target="#ref_BSOAS"/><biblScope>XVII
                    479</biblScope></bibl>).</note>
                <note type="footnote" xml:lang="en" n="1"><bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Gershevitch"/></bibl> traces %ifyc-%i back to %ipaxš-%i, as
                    he traces %idūc-%i [see <ref type="xr" target="#entry_dūcyn"/>] back to
                    %iduxš-%i (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_BSOAS"/><biblScope>XVII
                            479</biblScope></bibl>).</note>
            </entry>
        </body>
    </text>
